WEBVTT

01:46.606 --> 01:49.109
<i>An additional landing?</i>

01:49.192 --> 01:50.193
<i>Yes.</i>

01:50.276 --> 01:53.530
Two days have passed, and no one
has returned with the elixir.

01:53.613 --> 01:54.447
Two days...

01:54.531 --> 01:56.199
This next group will be incredible.

01:56.282 --> 01:57.575
After all,

01:57.659 --> 02:00.703
it includes Yamada Asaemon Shugen

02:00.787 --> 02:03.206
and four elite Iwagakure ninjas.

02:03.289 --> 02:06.543
<i>Including their subordinates,
more than 50 people.</i>

02:06.626 --> 02:09.337
For the advance team,
it’s practically a treasure ship.

02:09.420 --> 02:11.589
<i>That fool of a lord.</i>

02:11.673 --> 02:15.593
<i>Why gather this much manpower
for a task like this?</i>

02:15.677 --> 02:18.805
<i>The ninja chief
must have an ulterior motive.</i>

02:19.389 --> 02:20.598
Aoki-dono.

02:21.558 --> 02:22.809
Is something troubling you?

02:23.434 --> 02:26.479
Even if we meet troubled waters,
we will be standing by.

02:26.563 --> 02:30.233
But can you really
control this many people?

02:30.316 --> 02:31.484
And...

02:32.652 --> 02:34.737
those two over there
have no rank, do they?

02:35.446 --> 02:36.906
There’s no need for concern.

02:36.990 --> 02:39.993
That young man is Yamada Asaemon Kiyomaru.

02:40.076 --> 02:43.037
He lacks a rank
only because he’s not yet of age,

02:43.121 --> 02:45.999
but his ability rivals the top
one or two among the disciples.

02:46.583 --> 02:48.418
This is Yamada Asaemon Isuzu.

02:48.501 --> 02:50.753
Though a woman, she’s strong
and wields a massive blade.

02:51.504 --> 02:53.840
She served in a special capacity
under the shogunate.

02:54.340 --> 02:59.053
They’re known as "Ura-yurushi."
By rule, they hold no rank,

02:59.137 --> 03:02.640
but their skill is equal to those
with full licensure, the "Oku-yurushi."

03:03.224 --> 03:04.976
We also have Jikka-dono,
whose skills are unquestionable.

03:05.059 --> 03:07.020
Yes, my <i>skills</i> are unquestionable.

03:07.604 --> 03:10.940
We have no intention
of remaining mere overseers.

03:11.566 --> 03:14.027
We intend to give this our all
for the sake of our comrades as well.

03:14.903 --> 03:16.154
I see.

03:16.237 --> 03:19.991
If you’re worried, shall I demonstrate
my swordsmanship? You old bastard.

03:20.074 --> 03:21.159
Hey... Kiyo-chan!

03:21.242 --> 03:23.786
They look down on me
just because I don't have a rank.

03:24.370 --> 03:27.540
So damn irritating.
I’m definitely stronger than him too.

03:27.624 --> 03:29.292
But you can't...

03:31.836 --> 03:34.881
If you like, I could
cut down everyone here.

03:36.090 --> 03:37.383
Feel free.

03:43.223 --> 03:46.142
Huh? I deliberately cut next to him,

03:46.226 --> 03:49.145
but he really didn't move. No fun.

03:50.605 --> 03:55.109
That’s rude to the ninja.
Sheathe your sword, Kiyo-chan.

03:56.110 --> 03:58.029
You too, big woman.

04:03.493 --> 04:05.578
<i>Will these two really be okay?</i>

04:05.662 --> 04:06.663
No, no, no.

04:07.247 --> 04:11.042
It won’t do for samurai
to quarrel over something like this.

04:11.626 --> 04:13.544
Please don’t concern yourselves with us.

04:13.628 --> 04:16.923
O-our apologies for such
an embarrassing display!

04:17.507 --> 04:20.343
No. A shinobi’s life
belongs to their master.

04:20.927 --> 04:23.554
On this mission, Yamada is our master.

04:23.638 --> 04:26.432
If you doubt us,
please name anyone you like.

04:27.058 --> 04:30.561
That person can either disembark
or be struck down for their insolence,

04:31.187 --> 04:33.481
to demonstrate our loyalty to our master.

04:36.025 --> 04:38.194
You then. Show me.

04:38.778 --> 04:39.696
A ninja's loyalty.

04:41.781 --> 04:43.324
- Understood.
- Oh?

04:44.284 --> 04:45.326
I’ll leave the rest to you.

04:47.287 --> 04:51.582
<i>Toryanse, toryanse</i>

04:51.666 --> 04:56.587
<i>This narrow path, where does it lead?</i>

04:56.671 --> 04:59.924
<i>Does the angel's</i>

05:00.008 --> 05:02.218
<i>Path...</i>

05:09.058 --> 05:13.604
Shinobi have no individual will or heart.

05:13.688 --> 05:16.107
To exist solely as tools,
that is our true calling.

05:16.983 --> 05:18.860
Please, place your trust in us.

05:18.943 --> 05:21.446
T-that’s enough. Everyone, return.

05:21.529 --> 05:23.906
What resolve! I’m deeply impressed!

05:23.990 --> 05:26.200
I really don’t get ninja.

05:29.120 --> 05:32.665
Infiltrate the mission and kill Gabimaru.

05:33.333 --> 05:36.127
I never imagined
I’d be assigned such a task

05:36.210 --> 05:39.672
before an assassin could kill him
at the execution grounds.

05:39.756 --> 05:43.718
You must kill him,
or you'll never settle things.

05:44.343 --> 05:47.180
Kill Gabimaru, no matter what.

05:47.263 --> 05:51.267
<i>Your lives exist solely for that purpose.</i>

05:51.851 --> 05:53.269
Are you sure, Shugen?

05:53.853 --> 05:55.438
Trusting people like that?

05:55.521 --> 05:58.191
I never trusted them to begin with.

05:58.274 --> 06:00.068
Rogue ninja are no different
from criminals.

06:00.777 --> 06:02.779
We’ll find the elixir ourselves.

06:03.821 --> 06:04.906
The Asaemon alone.

06:04.989 --> 06:07.658
Then, what about the criminals
already on the island?

06:08.242 --> 06:11.245
Any condemned criminals found
will be executed on sight.

06:11.871 --> 06:14.165
All Asaemon will be brought back by me.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.668
<i>Eizen-dono... Everyone...</i>

06:18.419 --> 06:19.921
<i>Please be safe.</i>

06:21.380 --> 06:22.423
Man...

06:22.507 --> 06:25.301
Management really is tough, huh?

06:25.384 --> 06:29.972
When you’re dealing with so many oddballs,
it must interfere with the mission itself.

06:30.056 --> 06:31.432
It can’t be helped.

06:31.516 --> 06:35.061
The shogun expects
swift completion this way.

06:35.144 --> 06:39.273
It's a treasure ship carrying allies
for the advance party.

06:40.274 --> 06:42.276
You’re joking, right?

06:42.360 --> 06:46.364
This boat isn't carrying allies.

06:46.906 --> 06:49.784
<i>Just more death and chaos.</i>

06:49.867 --> 06:52.411
<i>It's like a ship of mistaken dreams.</i>

06:52.495 --> 06:55.456
<i>A vessel that carries
nightmares and calamity.</i>

06:57.750 --> 07:00.670
<i>More, more, and more will die.</i>

07:01.879 --> 07:04.215
<i>Not a single one will return.</i>

07:08.219 --> 07:09.428
<i>Additional landing?</i>

07:10.847 --> 07:12.473
It might be Shugen and the others.

07:13.057 --> 07:16.811
They’re reserve Asaemon chosen
by Eizen under shogunate orders.

07:16.894 --> 07:19.939
If it’s Shu, he should be able to control
even the condemned criminals.

07:20.523 --> 07:22.567
Will this Shugen guy be on our side?

07:22.650 --> 07:24.527
Yes, I’m sure of it.

07:24.610 --> 07:26.696
<i>He’s the strongest in the Yamada clan.</i>

07:27.321 --> 07:29.282
<i>His practical swordsmanship is first-rate.</i>

07:30.366 --> 07:33.286
<i>Being first-rate alone
won’t let you survive this island.</i>

07:33.911 --> 07:36.038
You need to use
that Tao magic or whatever.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.457
It’s not magic!

07:37.540 --> 07:38.749
If it’s Shugen,

07:38.833 --> 07:41.377
he should already be able to perceive Tao.

07:42.211 --> 07:46.757
<i>While training together, he seemed
to notice the sense I possess as well.</i>

07:46.841 --> 07:48.634
<i>He's a man who's earnest to the core.</i>

07:49.218 --> 07:51.762
<i>He was eager to learn from me.</i>

07:52.513 --> 07:54.140
<i>He was the one who named it "waves."</i>

07:54.807 --> 07:55.892
Isuzu.

07:55.975 --> 07:57.268
Hold on to this.

07:57.351 --> 08:00.021
What?! But how will you fight
without a weapon?

08:00.104 --> 08:01.522
You’ll get eaten!

08:01.606 --> 08:04.984
That sword is a masterpiece
bestowed by the shogun himself.

08:05.610 --> 08:07.195
It’s a symbol of official duty.

08:10.573 --> 08:12.116
I won’t use it to hunt boars.

08:15.286 --> 08:17.413
I learned this from Fuchi-kun.

08:17.497 --> 08:21.834
You can infer muscle structure and tension
to some extent just by appearance.

08:21.918 --> 08:24.378
<i>And using that knowledge, dismantling
or destroying a body becomes easy.</i>

08:27.465 --> 08:29.634
And I learned this from Shion-dono.

08:30.218 --> 08:31.469
By seeing the "waves,"

08:31.552 --> 08:33.638
you can infer
the structure of life itself.

08:43.022 --> 08:45.566
If he’s that strong, that’s reassuring.

08:46.984 --> 08:48.528
What is it, Sensei?

08:49.028 --> 08:51.656
I think I might know him.

08:51.739 --> 08:53.699
Yamada Asaemon Shugen...

08:54.283 --> 08:55.826
He’s the one from that incident, right?

08:55.910 --> 08:58.829
Incident? Did he cause
trouble or something?

08:58.913 --> 09:02.041
N-no... It’s not that
it was trouble exactly.

09:02.625 --> 09:05.586
He can just be excessively strict.

09:06.212 --> 09:07.588
What kind of incident?

09:08.214 --> 09:10.091
This is just what I've heard, but...

09:10.675 --> 09:15.096
<i>When the boss of the infamous Edo yakuza,
the Ginhebi family, was captured,</i>

09:15.763 --> 09:19.559
<i>he stubbornly refused to reveal
where his subordinates were hidden,</i>

09:19.642 --> 09:21.811
<i>and the officials were at a loss.</i>

09:22.520 --> 09:24.105
<i>That’s when Shugen-dono was summoned.</i>

09:24.939 --> 09:28.067
<i>He beheaded one already-captured
subordinate right before his eyes,</i>

09:28.150 --> 09:29.735
<i>forced him to talk,</i>

09:29.819 --> 09:34.115
<i>and including those found, he executed
all 20 members of the Ginhebi family.</i>

09:35.116 --> 09:38.119
Delighted by the spectacle,

09:38.202 --> 09:40.079
<i>the shogun granted him special attire</i>

09:40.162 --> 09:42.456
<i>and the famous blade "Fuributsu Kaneaki,"</i>

09:42.540 --> 09:45.626
<i>and from then on, he gained
influence within the shogunate.</i>

09:49.213 --> 09:50.881
So, he slaughtered all the criminals, huh?

09:52.216 --> 09:54.510
<i>That’s pretty badass.</i>

09:55.094 --> 09:58.639
He’s a good person at heart.
He’s kind to all his disciples.

09:58.723 --> 10:00.725
He was Sagi’s first love, after all.

10:02.727 --> 10:04.353
What's the story there?

10:04.437 --> 10:06.147
Do you want to be his bride?

10:06.230 --> 10:07.440
No, that’s...

10:09.066 --> 10:10.818
It was just when I was a child.

10:10.901 --> 10:13.154
I did admire him.

10:14.989 --> 10:19.660
And the reason I was permitted
a Yamada rank was thanks to Shugen-dono.

10:20.578 --> 10:23.247
Please grant Sagiri a rank as well.

10:24.248 --> 10:26.667
If you won't acknowledge her superb skill,

10:26.751 --> 10:29.170
then I cannot take pride in my own rank.

10:29.754 --> 10:32.715
<i>He's hard-headed, but kind.</i>

10:33.507 --> 10:35.176
Shugen, are you hurt?

10:35.259 --> 10:37.637
If you’d just said something,
we would have...

10:37.720 --> 10:41.057
Our orders from the shogunate
are strictly to monitor and execute.

10:43.059 --> 10:46.479
There’s no need to stain your blades
with anything beyond that.

10:47.229 --> 10:49.440
Leave trivial matters
to your senior disciples.

10:50.566 --> 10:53.235
Your eyes look scary even when you smile.

10:53.944 --> 10:55.321
They do?

10:55.404 --> 10:58.491
Man, he’s reliable, isn't he?

10:58.574 --> 11:00.701
Jikka-dono, you’re older
than I am, aren’t you?

11:01.952 --> 11:03.454
Let's hurry on.

11:07.208 --> 11:10.127
Once he understands the situation,
I’m sure he’ll help us.

11:10.211 --> 11:12.254
No, we can't believe that.

11:13.881 --> 11:15.216
About what you said earlier...

11:16.008 --> 11:17.927
You’re a little mistaken.

11:18.844 --> 11:20.846
It’s a sensitive topic,
even within the Yamada clan.

11:20.930 --> 11:21.764
Huh?

11:22.473 --> 11:25.309
The ones Shugen executed
weren’t just 20 yakuza,

11:25.810 --> 11:27.019
it was the entire family.

11:27.103 --> 11:28.437
Yes...

11:28.521 --> 11:30.022
So, it was 20.

11:30.106 --> 11:31.524
<i>No.</i>

11:31.607 --> 11:33.901
<i>Twenty Ginhebi members and their families.</i>

11:34.527 --> 11:37.154
<i>Their relatives, elderly parents,</i>

11:37.238 --> 11:38.614
<i>even small children.</i>

11:39.407 --> 11:40.908
<i>More than 100 people in total.</i>

11:42.326 --> 11:45.496
How could he... Yataro... This is...

11:45.579 --> 11:48.249
He's just a child!

11:48.332 --> 11:51.544
Was it really necessary to go this far?!

11:52.878 --> 11:55.172
It’s tragic, but unavoidable.

11:55.256 --> 11:57.174
If only you are executed,

11:57.258 --> 12:00.010
your business will simply
be passed on to your family, won't it?

12:00.636 --> 12:03.305
Evil arises not only
from an individual’s heart,

12:03.389 --> 12:05.474
but from the environment
in which they were raised.

12:06.684 --> 12:07.643
At the very least,

12:08.185 --> 12:10.938
I pray that in your next life,
you’ll be reborn as good people!

12:11.021 --> 12:13.441
He’s not human... Not human...

12:13.524 --> 12:14.692
Not human...

12:19.780 --> 12:21.699
As a samurai, I like him,

12:22.283 --> 12:23.576
and he’s my friend.

12:23.659 --> 12:25.244
But I'm sure

12:25.327 --> 12:28.122
Shugen would never forgive
any condemned criminal.

12:28.789 --> 12:29.832
No matter the circumstances.

12:32.793 --> 12:36.755
He wouldn’t even forgive an Asaemon
who sheltered a criminal, would he?

12:38.007 --> 12:39.550
<i>That’s the kind of man he is.</i>

12:41.385 --> 12:43.554
<i>Once he learns
what’s happening on the island,</i>

12:43.637 --> 12:44.847
<i>even more so.</i>

12:47.183 --> 12:49.435
Your name is... Shugen?

12:49.518 --> 12:52.021
You, whose parents
were murdered at a young age,

12:52.521 --> 12:54.773
being taken in here by fate...

12:55.774 --> 12:58.444
Official duty will surely
be painful for you.

12:59.111 --> 13:01.447
You’ll come face to face
with many kinds of "sin."

13:01.530 --> 13:04.825
They still haven't caught the person
who killed my parents.

13:04.909 --> 13:07.912
I might get to cut off their head someday.

13:08.913 --> 13:13.209
The Yamada Asaemon ideal is a single
strike devoid of pain and emotion, right?

13:14.585 --> 13:15.711
That’s correct.

13:16.629 --> 13:20.007
I can’t understand that.
A sword should be dull.

13:20.508 --> 13:22.968
Cut again and again
until the head comes off.

13:23.052 --> 13:25.346
That would make them
suffer more before they die, right?

13:26.138 --> 13:28.849
Why don't I just blunt a blade
and make it jagged?

13:29.725 --> 13:31.101
- That’s pointless.
- Huh?

13:31.685 --> 13:33.103
Because I'll just sharpen it.

13:36.524 --> 13:39.568
<i>Erasing hatred instantly may be difficult,</i>

13:39.652 --> 13:43.405
<i>but by learning and teaching here,
you’ll come to understand how to face it.</i>

13:45.533 --> 13:48.369
<i>And if you still want to blunt
the blade, then do so.</i>

13:48.994 --> 13:50.454
<i>I'll sharpen it again and again.</i>

13:52.665 --> 13:55.459
<i>Someday, a beautiful hamon will appear.</i>

13:56.418 --> 13:57.628
I look forward to it.

14:01.173 --> 14:03.717
Eizen-dono! I...

14:04.468 --> 14:06.220
I still haven't...

14:08.639 --> 14:10.307
- Shugen...
- I still haven't...

14:10.391 --> 14:12.560
It’s painful, but let’s move on.

14:13.686 --> 14:16.355
I’m worried about the others’ safety too.

14:17.189 --> 14:18.857
Yeah... You’re right...

14:21.735 --> 14:24.321
Let’s at least finish the rites... then go.

14:24.864 --> 14:25.698
Okay.

14:32.955 --> 14:34.999
<i>What strange people.</i>

14:35.082 --> 14:38.335
<i>Reading sutras so calmly
on a monster-filled island.</i>

14:38.419 --> 14:40.337
<i>But those two following him
are strange as well.</i>

14:41.005 --> 14:43.340
<i>Is he really that extraordinary a man?</i>

14:43.924 --> 14:47.094
<i>No, if we’re talking strange,
then this man too...</i>

14:47.761 --> 14:49.471
<i>I can’t read what’s going on
in his head at all.</i>

14:50.389 --> 14:52.057
<i>I wanna go home.</i>

14:52.141 --> 14:53.100
<i>But</i>

14:53.183 --> 14:56.562
<i>this dangerous island is convenient
for outmaneuvering the Asaemon.</i>

14:56.645 --> 14:59.815
<i>I’ll seize an opening and achieve my goal.</i>

14:59.899 --> 15:03.569
<i>That man won’t die on an island like this.</i>

15:10.451 --> 15:13.621
Whoa, another huge one.

15:23.464 --> 15:26.800
Capture them alive if possible.

15:26.884 --> 15:28.969
It talks... A different species?

15:29.053 --> 15:31.180
If you can talk, then let's negotiate.

15:31.263 --> 15:33.432
I don’t have that authority.

15:33.515 --> 15:35.142
Take it up with the Tensen.

15:40.105 --> 15:43.525
Hey! Shugen’s in the middle of mourning!

15:58.999 --> 16:00.417
<i>Its center of gravity is off.</i>

16:12.721 --> 16:14.640
There’s more coming, Kiyo-chan!

16:14.723 --> 16:16.392
Yeah, I know! You're so loud!

16:16.475 --> 16:19.728
- Magnificent technique.
- Right?

16:19.812 --> 16:21.146
Let's join them.

16:21.230 --> 16:23.148
Arakagi, bring that one down.

16:23.941 --> 16:24.775
Understood.

16:31.073 --> 16:34.159
Bakuro group, Ishi-Fudo group, move.

16:35.869 --> 16:38.288
Individually, we may not rival Yamada,

16:39.206 --> 16:40.374
but shinobi are a colony.

16:40.457 --> 16:42.418
We accomplish things through numbers.

16:43.168 --> 16:46.588
Individual strength eventually
bows to numerical strength.

16:46.672 --> 16:49.425
No hero can overcome numbers.

16:50.884 --> 16:54.054
This is how lesser shinobi fight.

16:54.638 --> 16:56.807
"Lesser," huh?

17:08.736 --> 17:10.112
May you rest in peace...

17:12.281 --> 17:13.490
Shugen!

17:27.755 --> 17:29.339
Awesome.

17:39.016 --> 17:40.225
You monsters.

17:41.226 --> 17:44.772
No, everything living on this island...

17:44.855 --> 17:49.276
I’ll slaughter all of you
as painfully as possible.

17:50.277 --> 17:51.236
Very well.

17:54.490 --> 17:56.909
I’ll kill you and take you as a gift,

17:58.744 --> 18:01.497
to earn my promotion to "Chisen."

18:10.881 --> 18:14.760
Even your regenerative ability
has its limits, huh?

18:15.928 --> 18:20.015
If you don’t answer my questions,
or if I dislike your answers,

18:20.599 --> 18:21.683
I’ll carve you up.

18:22.601 --> 18:24.978
First, your comrades.

18:25.062 --> 18:27.648
If you’re part of an organization,
explain it in detail.

18:27.731 --> 18:29.566
Uh... Well...

18:30.317 --> 18:33.403
Don’t hesitate to say.
You’re wasting time.

18:33.487 --> 18:35.948
Now, now, Shugen.

18:36.031 --> 18:38.242
Since we've discovered
a new species of monster,

18:38.325 --> 18:41.537
why don’t we return
to the mainland for now and report?

18:41.620 --> 18:43.080
I refuse!

18:43.163 --> 18:46.166
You just want to go home,
don’t you, Jikka-dono?

18:46.250 --> 18:48.418
You didn’t draw
your sword just now, either.

18:49.962 --> 18:52.339
I can’t draw it. You know that.

18:52.923 --> 18:55.342
You can draw it. I know you can.

18:55.425 --> 18:59.596
Calm down, Shugen.
The two of you fighting won't...

18:59.680 --> 19:00.848
You’re right.

19:05.894 --> 19:10.065
My apologies. I spoke disrespectfully
to my senior in my agitation.

19:10.149 --> 19:13.694
Ah, it’s fine, it’s fine. I don’t mind.

19:14.736 --> 19:16.238
Sorry to you two as well.

19:16.321 --> 19:19.199
<i>- He looks funny doing that.</i>
- Kiyo-chan!

19:19.283 --> 19:22.828
But if we return without settling matters,

19:22.911 --> 19:26.456
it would tarnish the family name
and Eizen-dono's honor.

19:27.040 --> 19:29.751
The island’s creatures must be eradicated.

19:29.835 --> 19:32.838
We must show what happens
when you lay hands on a Yamada disciple.

19:35.674 --> 19:37.843
For that, information is essential.

19:38.802 --> 19:42.472
Shugen. In terms
of interrogation and torture,

19:42.556 --> 19:45.017
please leave it to the shinobi.

19:46.894 --> 19:49.771
What appears like mist
is dense particles of Tao.

19:50.522 --> 19:53.233
Even though it allows us to sense
abnormalities on the island,

19:53.817 --> 19:56.737
it doesn't tell us the identities
of the newcomers.

19:57.362 --> 19:58.989
I’m sorry.

19:59.072 --> 20:02.743
First the Tensen, now new visitors.

20:03.410 --> 20:05.954
The more time passes,
the more complicated this gets.

20:06.955 --> 20:09.875
From here on, I think it’s better
to split into two groups.

20:10.542 --> 20:11.627
Two groups?

20:11.710 --> 20:15.380
One group goes for the elixir,
the other secures an escape route.

20:15.464 --> 20:18.550
What?! Then I’m definitely
on the escape team.

20:18.634 --> 20:20.636
It’s the "escape route securing team."

20:21.261 --> 20:23.513
Based on the route Mei told us about,

20:23.597 --> 20:25.766
we’ll pass through
Horai’s interior either way.

20:25.849 --> 20:28.518
What? Why not just leave from the beach?

20:28.602 --> 20:30.270
There are monsters in the sea too.

20:31.146 --> 20:33.482
Are you saying you have
a countermeasure for the Tensen?

20:33.565 --> 20:35.609
Based on my hypothesis.

20:36.276 --> 20:37.361
I confirmed it with her as well.

20:40.572 --> 20:44.701
Tao has attributes.
Each attribute has compatibilities,

20:44.785 --> 20:46.912
advantages, and disadvantages.

20:46.995 --> 20:49.706
By exploiting them,
we can weaken the enemy’s Tao

20:49.790 --> 20:52.251
and strengthen our own.

20:52.334 --> 20:54.753
No matter how transcendent they are,

20:54.836 --> 20:57.297
as long as Tao is their source of power,

20:57.381 --> 20:59.007
they can’t escape this rule.

20:59.841 --> 21:02.010
It will work on them too.

21:02.094 --> 21:03.762
This makes no sense.

21:04.471 --> 21:07.057
How much will this work?

21:07.140 --> 21:09.268
Is there any guarantee we won’t die?

21:09.351 --> 21:12.271
Charging into the enemy’s nest
like that is way too dangerous.

21:12.938 --> 21:16.817
Wouldn’t it be more realistic
to just leave the island and disappear?

21:16.900 --> 21:19.987
Which means it would
be better to move alone.

21:21.488 --> 21:23.448
Yuzuriha has a point.

21:23.532 --> 21:27.035
In the end, we’re just a group
brought together by circumstance.

21:28.120 --> 21:31.456
There’s no inherent bond
or obligation between us.

21:31.540 --> 21:33.667
<i>There are too many uncertainties.</i>

21:33.750 --> 21:36.503
<i>Who are the new arrivals?</i>

21:37.963 --> 21:38.922
<i>Or perhaps...</i>

21:40.132 --> 21:42.301
<i>there may be unforeseen factors.</i>

21:42.384 --> 21:44.303
<i>From here on, we can’t
predict what will happen</i>

21:44.386 --> 21:47.014
<i>or who will lose their life.</i>

21:49.016 --> 21:51.935
So, it’s better for each person

21:52.561 --> 21:54.313
to decide what to do on their own.

21:54.396 --> 21:56.898
Those who wish to come together,
meet at the cave.

21:56.982 --> 21:59.776
If you choose to act alone, that’s fine.

22:00.610 --> 22:02.279
I won’t question your position.

22:06.783 --> 22:09.578
Uh... Well...

22:10.203 --> 22:12.456
Shouldn’t we...

22:13.290 --> 22:17.210
think about this a bit more?
That was way too quick a decision.

22:17.294 --> 22:19.838
We’ve come this far.
Might as well stick together, right?

22:19.921 --> 22:23.216
As long as I get home,
I don’t really care.

22:23.300 --> 22:24.968
More shields is better.

22:25.052 --> 22:28.972
I don’t really get it, but we can probably
take down one lousy Tensen, right?

22:31.683 --> 22:33.435
That was a pointless question.

22:33.518 --> 22:36.855
If you intend to return home,
cooperating is the most rational choice.

22:36.938 --> 22:39.608
We’ll simply carry out our duty.

22:39.691 --> 22:41.860
We’ll see it through to the end.

22:43.195 --> 22:44.112
I mean,

22:44.196 --> 22:46.448
are you planning
on splitting up from me, Sensei?!

22:46.531 --> 22:48.366
That wasn’t my intention.

22:48.450 --> 22:49.618
I know, but still!

22:49.701 --> 22:53.330
Even if we get the elixir,
only one person gets exonerated.

22:53.413 --> 22:55.499
Let’s fight over it on the return ship.

22:56.083 --> 22:57.834
Honestly, I feel relieved.

22:58.877 --> 23:00.337
The more comrades, the better.

23:00.921 --> 23:02.339
Let’s all escape together.

23:03.048 --> 23:06.176
<i>With the situation at its most confused,
this moment right now</i>

23:06.259 --> 23:08.220
<i>is our greatest and final, chance!</i>

24:23.336 --> 24:25.922
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman
